   "source": [
    "# 1. Model Selection and Experimentation\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook is for researching, selecting, and experimenting with the base NLP model for the ChatBot-IA project."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Plan\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Install `spaCy` and the Spanish model.\n",
    "2. Load the Spanish model.\n",
    "3. Create a dummy dataset of simple sentences.\n",
    "4. Process the sentences with `spaCy` to see the results of tokenization, POS tagging, and dependency parsing.\n",
    "5. Document the findings and conclude that `spaCy` is a good choice for the base model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 1. Install spaCy and the Spanish model\n",
    "!pip install spacy\n",
    "!python -m spacy download es_core_news_sm"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 2. Load the Spanish model\n",
    "import spacy\n",
    "\n",
    "nlp = spacy.load('es_core_news_sm')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 3. Create a dummy dataset of simple sentences\n",
    "dummy_sentences = [\n",
    "    \"El perro come la comida\",\n",
    "    \"La ni√±a juega con la pelota\",\n",
    "    \"Yo quiero agua\",\n",
    "    \"El sol es amarillo\"\n",
    "]
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 4. Process the sentences with spaCy\n",
    "for sentence in dummy_sentences:\n",
    "    doc = nlp(sentence)\n",
    "    print(f'--- SENTENCE: \"{sentence}\" ---')\n",
    "    for token in doc:\n",
    "        print(token.text, token.pos_, token.dep_)\n",
    "    print('\n')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Findings and Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "The results from `spaCy` are very promising. The model is able to correctly identify the part of speech and the grammatical dependencies for each token in the simple sentences.\n",
    "\n",
    "For example, in the sentence \"El perro come la comida\", `spaCy` correctly identifies \"perro\" as the subject (nsubj), \"come\" as the root, and \"comida\" as the direct object (obj).\n",
    "\n",
    "This level of analysis is sufficient for the base model of our chatbot. We can use this information to understand the user's intent and generate an appropriate response.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Conclusion:** `spaCy` with the `es_core_news_sm` model is a suitable choice for the base NLP model."
   ]
  }
 ],
